name: Ulta Beauty
directions: In the back of the store on the right, by the salon.
comment: The two gendered restrooms are single occupancy and have a private hallway, no one will see which one you go in.

name: Elk cafe
directions: Back past the bar

name: A&E Coffee Roasters
directions: Directly inside the main door on the right.
comment: I don't know that you need to order anything but the coffee is good.

name: Kelsey Museum of Archaeology
directions: On the first floor in the older part of the building away from the artifacts. Accessible through the gift shop
comment: The museum is free and on one of the main streets in Ann Arbor

name: Kelsey Museum of Archaeology
directions: On the first floor in the older part of the building away from the artifacts. Accessible through the gift shop
comment: The museum is free and on one of the main streets in Ann Arbor

name: Voxman Music Building
directions: 2nd floor, find the gendered restrooms and go straight through the double doors. This leads to backstage of the concert hall, but in the little area on the other side of the doors is a unisex restroom.

name: Tartine Manufactury
directions: Go in accessible entry on 18th st and past bakery towards sign that says "boiler room". In a small hallway just before the sign are 4 gender neutral single stall restrooms.
comment: Tartine Manufactory main address is on Alabama st, but ignore that or you'll have to go through the crowded restaurant.

name: Target
directions: To the left of the entry, first door in the hall behind customer service
comment: Both unisex "family" single stall bathroom and men's room has many stalls. Sometimes a bit dirty.

name: Shenandoah University Brandt Student Center
directions: Behind the information desk near the offices

name: New York Historical Society
directions: First floor
comment: Need to be paying costumer as there isn't a way to get back to it without ticket

name: Murray-Aikins Dining Hall
directions: On the first floor, one restroom on the right just past the swipe-in area. On the second floor, two restrooms up the stairs and straight ahead.
comment: To use the one on the first floor, either swipe in/pay first or just ask if you can use the restroom.

name: Alamo Drafthouse
directions: By escalators just right of House of Wax bar  / single and separate from men's/women's
comment: Don't need to be a paying customer just walk past front desk just beyond escalator

name: BP
directions: To the left of the front door.
comment:
Sign says for customers only, but it is a gas station, so there's plenty of cheap items. 
Not very clean, but everything works.

name: Murray-Aikins Dining Hall
directions: One on the first floor on the right when you enter the dining hall, two upstairs and straight ahead
comment: To use the one on the first floor, either swipe in/pay to eat at the dining hall or just ask the person at the cash register if you can just use the bathroom

name: Murray-Aikins Dining Hall
directions: One on the first floor on the right when you enter the dining hall, two upstairs and straight ahead
comment: To use the one on the first floor, either swipe in/pay to eat at the dining hall or just ask the person at the cash register if you can just use the bathroom

name: Taco Del Mar
directions: Taco del Mar is in the Bales Thriftway parking mall area. It is between Subway and Dairy Queen. The bathrooms are in the back right of the store.
comment: These bathrooms are gendered men and women but they are single stall that lock. The staff don't really care who uses them and who enters which room can only be seen by very few because they're in a separate hallway.

name: Century Chiropractic Center
directions: Straight through the front door, right at the first hallway. The door is on your left, opposite a long mirror.
comment: This is actually 3 small businesses, but they're divided inside the building. The restroom is shared between them. If the door opens fully, it bangs into the mirror across the hall, so close the door after you leave, and knock before you open it.

name: Costa Coffee - Balsall Common
directions: Walk towards the back of the shop and it should be on your left, there will be a sign
comment: I'm not sure but you may have to be a paying customer, there are small snacks or bottled drinks if you have to buy something

name: The Coronet
comment: single room with vertical and horizontal grab bars by toilet.

name: Orpheum Theatre
directions: First floor, next to theatre two another one in front of the hallway
comment: Well you have to be going to a movie there. Overall pretty inclusive, although 'gendered' restrooms no one will care which one you go in, and private stalls inside

name: Co-op La Maison Verte
directions: Back and to the right of store.
comment: Inclusive health food and natural products cafe/general store. Staff not always the warmest, but def a safe place welcoming to all. Kid friendly.

name: Target Packards Corner
comment: Just need to ask a team member for access, two unisex/gender-neutral single room bathrooms

name: Pita Jungle
comment: has vertical and horizontal grab bar by toilet

name: Watercourse Way Bathouse and Spa
directions: Right of the buddha statue/waterfall through the archway. The two doors on your left.
comment: They are technically for customers, but nobody monitors them, and you're welcome to browse the little shop out front. Just don't be loud or stinky and nobody will bat an eyelash.

name: Our bookshop
directions: First floor towards the back (Next to sci-fi, right before the stairs)
comment: Definitely the best bathroom in saugerties, hands down. Regardless of gender, class, or whatever else, I highly reccomend taking a shit here. Most interesting bathroom experience. 10/10

name: Maplefields
directions: Maplefield's on the right past exit 18 exit ramp. Bathrooms are on the left past the ATM when you enter the business.
comment: You do not need to be a paying customer.

name: Jewel
directions: Near registers
comment: Bathrooms are gendered but single occupancy

name: Jewel Osco
directions: Go into store and turn left
comment: Bathrooms are gendered but single occupancy

name: Home Depot
comment: has horizontal and vertical grab bar

name: Hillerød Bibliotek
directions: Første sal, i rum overfor indgang

name: Bean Scene Cafe
comment: For customers only

name: Vassar College
comment: Most of the campus bathrooms are gender neutral, especially all the ones in dorms, and they recently made the second floor bathroom in Main building gender neutral and it's the nicest bathroom in campus

name: Target
directions: Front doors to the left immediately before the fan merchandise area.
comment: There's a family/unisex bathroom right across from water fountain

name: Elliot College
directions: Next to Mungos Bar

name: Johnny Carino's
directions: Back left corner when you walk in.
comment: I work at Johnny Carino's and I can vouch that you will always be able to use your preferred restroom without fear. More of our staff is LGBTQ+ than not, and if any of our managers caught someone harassing you for using your preferred restroom, they would be asked to leave.

name: REI
comment: If you feel uncomfortable using the gendered bathrooms, you may ask a sales associate to use the employee single stall. :)

name: Dr. Insomniac's Fine Coffee, Tea, Smoothies & Cafe
comment: It's a cafe, so you have to get something - great coffee :)

name: Hotel Allegro
directions: Second floor, walk up the stairs and take a right past the fire place, and heading towards 312 hotel. there are gendered and non gendered options.

name: Skaf's Lebanese Cuisine
directions: Directly across from the rear entrance
comment: Not sure if it's for customers only

name: Akron Art Museum
directions: Second floor
comment: Two unmarked bathrooms

name: Reverie
directions: Bathrooms have a picture of a toilet + urinal on one door, and a toilet + baby changing table on the other, instead of traditional male/female figures.
comment: The staff all seem pretty awesome and accepting.

name: Reverie
directions: Bathrooms have a picture of a toilet + urinal on one door, and a toilet + baby changing table on the other, instead of traditional male/female figures.
comment: The staff all seem pretty awesome and accepting.

name: Delicioso Deli and Bistro
directions: Behind counter (ask to use)
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Woodstock Day School
directions: Top and bottom floors of the cafe ( big metal building in centre of campus)
comment: You must be a student or a visitor to enter campus

name: Cafe Social in Uncommon
directions: Enter building through lobby entrance on corner of Bedford and Mifflin St. Go up the stairs and bathrooms are to the left.
comment: Bathroom is part of the lobby of the Uncommon apartments. Available to anyone during the hours of the coffee shop (7am-6:30p M-F; 9a-5p Sat and Sun)

name: Fred Meyers
directions: By entrance near gas station, two family restrooms.

name: Paramount Cafe
directions: Enter the cafe through the main door, go through to the section to the left, walk to the back, take a right and it's in the small room there.

name: Pizzuti Collection
directions: 1st and 2nd floor

name: Wash n' go laundromat
directions: Straight back, look to left
comment: Probably fine if you're not a paying customer

name: Screen Door
comment: Both single-toilet restrooms are gender neutral

name: Dartmouth Curling Club
directions: Take stairs to second floor. There is one at the top of the stairs away from the bar, and another in the "back room" beside the bar.
comment: You should probably be curling or act like you're planning to watch curling. Maybe hang out and have a beer or something. (jokes)

name: Brightwood Golf and Country Club
directions: In the front door of the club, under the canopy, the washroom is hidden in the hallway on your left, between the offices and the Ball Room.
comment: Not only is this bathroom Gender Neutral, it is also rarely used by anyone! Very tidy, well appointed and clean. You could run in and use the can and go without any problems. There is also a Bar and a Restaurant, and, you know, a Golf Course.

name: Spyglass Park
directions: Between parking lot and playground equipment.
comment: Doors are automatically locked at night. (No soap)

name: Starbucks
comment: Have to be paying customer but there's no key for the bathroom

name: Burlington Public Library
directions: On the left after you pass a display case coming in through the front door.
comment: Two gendered single stalls, but people are known to disregard the gendering when there is a line, so it's not really enforced.

name: Phoenix Coffee
directions: Down the stairs to the left
comment: Must go through cafe

name: Dartmouth Curling Club
directions: Take stairs to second floor. There is one at the top of the stairs away from the bar, and another in the "back room" beside the bar.

name: Clinton high school

name: Bull McCabes
directions: Back left single stall unisex bathroom

name: Half Price Books
directions: Two unisex single stalls in back of store.

name: Talent Historical Society

name: AutoZone

Gym with gender neutral (family) dressing room as well as gender neutral single stall 
bathrooms and in the gendered dressing rooms, dressing stalls and showers with privacy curtains.

name: The Quirky Feather Confectionery
directions:
You can enter the store either from the front on the corner of 116th & Guilford,
-OR- you can enter from the back (if you drove, this is more convenient).
Look for the atrium with Fanfare, they are the first door on the ground floor,
between the elevator and Fanfare. The door is usually wide open.
